essional Development Ribbon  2  Army Service Ribbon Overseas Service Ribbon  2  Career Path Mr  Simmons joined the National Guard in February 1980 where he was trained as a Truck driver and a Cav Scout  He went into the active Army in August 1983  He has served in many different jobs and places throughout the world to include  Chief  Admin NCO Army ROTC  Virginia Military Institute  Admin NCO ROO MS I Instructor Army ROTC  Edinboro University  PA  Defense Courier Service  STRATCOM Joint Orderly Room NE  Admin NCO  Protocol Korea  Community NEO Warden for Mainz Germany and Admin NCO 1 46 Inf  Fort Knox KY  Personal Mr  Simmons currently working on Associate Degree in Business Administration  Married to Jackie Simmons and have four children of which one is in the Navy and one in the VA National Guard  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 